Some scripts for an audio installation.

Recordings are triggered using a flic Bluetooth button.
Then, recordings are played back randomly on one of four different speakers.


Requirements:
  Python 2 (comes by default on Mac OS X)
  sox (for playing audio)
  ffmpeg (for recording audio)


settings.py: Settings for where to store the recordings, etc.

record-server.py: Listens for commands to record and stop recording.
  Stores the recordings in the recordings directory.

play.py: Plays back the recordings

start-recording.sh/stop-recording.sh: Scripts to be used to trigger
  starting/stopping recording.
  Meant to be called by a Flic Bluetooth button when the button is
  pressed/released, respectively.
